{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T04:43:37.417Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on the official resources from Multi-Agent Wiki, AWS documentation, and industry best practices, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Event fan-out for parallel agent activation\""},{"type":"text","text":" is an architectural pattern where "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"a single event triggers multiple agents to execute concurrently in parallel"},{"type":"text","text":", dramatically improving speed and scalability compared to sequential execution."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What It Is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Event fan-out is an "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"architectural pattern whereby a single source sends messages to multiple destinations simultaneously"},{"type":"text","text":", commonly implemented in pub/sub systems and parallel task queues."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Core Concept"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Single Event\n    ↓\nFan-out (distribute to multiple targets)\n    ↓\nAgent 1 → runs concurrently\nAgent 2 → runs concurrently\nAgent 3 → runs concurrently\n    ↓\nFan-in (gather + synthesize results)\n    ↓\nFinal output"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"In one line"},{"type":"text","text":": \"One input generates multiple outputs concurrently\"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Fan-Out / Gather Pattern"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Definition"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Parallel Fan-out / Gather"},{"type":"text","text":" splits a task across many agents in parallel; an aggregator merges the results."}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Phase"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What Happens"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fan-out"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Split task across multiple agents that execute concurrently"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Execute"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Branches share read-only context by default, never the workspace"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fan-in (Gather)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Aggregator merges, votes on, or synthesizes results"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Category"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Category"},{"type":"text","text":": Information flow"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Type"},{"type":"text","text":": Multi-agent pattern"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best for"},{"type":"text","text":": Multi-perspective exploration, parallel retrieval, parallel code reading, log analysis, model ensembling"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How Fan-Out Works: 5-Step Process"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 1: Trigger"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Single event occurs (user action, incoming message, scheduled job)\n    ↓\nInitiates distribution process"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 2: Task or Message Duplication"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"System determines targets\n    ↓\nPrepares message/workload for multiple recipients\nFor data processing: workload may be split into smaller independent tasks"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 3: Distribution"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Messages/workloads distributed to multiple consumers in parallel\n    ↓\nOften by message brokers or application logic"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 4: Parallel Processing"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each consumer processes assigned task concurrently in isolation\n    ↓\nSpecialized agents each handle distinct tasks parallel"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Efficiency"},{"type":"text","text":": Parallel processing reduces bottlenecks\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Scalability"},{"type":"text","text":": Agents scale independently based on their own queue depth\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Resilience"},{"type":"text","text":": Distributed processing reduces single points of failure\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Adaptability"},{"type":"text","text":": Real-time adjustments based on streaming data"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 5: Completion"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Process ends after all parallel tasks complete independently\n    ↓\nIf one branch fails: retried/handled independently while others continue"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation Approaches"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. AWS Step Functions (Map State)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Controller (Lambda/Step Function)\n    ↓\nDistributes subtasks using map state for parallel execution\n    ↓\nEach task invokes Bedrock LLM or subagent with its own prompt\n    ↓\nResults stored in S3/DynamoDB/queues\n    ↓\nAggregation step merges, compares, or filters outputs"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. AWS Lambda with Concurrency"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Event triggers Lambda\n    ↓\nLambda invokes multiple functions with concurrency\n    ↓\nEach function runs agent task independently\n    ↓\nCoordinator merges results from multiple invoked functions"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example"},{"type":"text","text":": \"If 500 research requests come in at once, you get 500 research agent functions running in parallel. The outline agents don't even notice. They're completely independent\"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. Amazon EventBridge"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Event先知 publishes to EventBridge topic\n    ↓\nMultiple subscribers (agents) receive event\n    ↓\nUse correlation IDs for tracking\n    ↓\nAggregation workflows merge results"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. Custom Controller Pattern"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Controller manages fan-out and gather\n    ↓\nUses S3, DynamoDB, or queues for coordination\n    ↓\nEach agent gets run id / trace id"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation Checklist"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Requirement"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Distinct goals"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Before fanning out, give each branch a distinct goal — avoid duplicated work"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Read-only context"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Branches share read-only context by default, never the workspace"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Deduplication"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Gather step does deduplication, conflict detection, evidence merging — not naive concatenation"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Concurrency config"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Configure concurrency, timeouts, cancellation, and budget caps"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Input/output schemas"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Defined for each agent"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Permission boundaries"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each agent's permission boundary defined"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Trace IDs"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Every agent call carries a run id / trace id"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Failure strategies"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Failure, timeout, cancel, and retry strategies defined"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Minimum context"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Context passed is minimum required, not full history"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"High-risk gating"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"High-risk actions are gated by approval or verifier"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Recommended Trace Events"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Track fan-out execution with these events:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"fanout.started\nbranch.started\nbranch.completed\nbranch.timeout\ngather.started\ngather.completed"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"When to Use Fan-Out"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ Use When"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Scenario"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why Works"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Strongly parallelizable tasks"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Agents can work independently"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Need multi-perspective exploration"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Different agents provide different viewpoints"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"High throughput required"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Parallel processing scales independently"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reduce latency"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Multiple agents work simultaneously instead of sequentially"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Independent agents"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Slow agents don't block fast agents"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"❌ Don't Use When"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Scenario"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Better Alternative"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Task is strongly order-dependent"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sequential execution"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Branches need shared mutable state"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Single agent with coordination"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Budget is tight"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sequential is cheaper (fewer parallel calls)"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fan-Out-on-Write vs Fan-Out-on-Read"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fan-Out-on-Write (Push Model)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Event occurs → System immediately pushes to all targets\n    ↓\nPre-distributes event upfront"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When"},{"type":"text","text":": Need immediate delivery to all subscribers"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fan-Out-on-Read (Pull Model)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Event occurs → System stores in single source feed\n    ↓\nConsumer requests event → System then distributes\n    ↓\nWithholds distribution until consumer requests"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When"},{"type":"text","text":": Subscribers have different rates, want on-demand fetching"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Real-World Use Cases"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use Case"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"How Fan-Out Works"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Research agents"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Multiple agents research different aspects of query"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Analysis pipelines"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Parallel transformations on same input"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Review systems"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Multiple agents review content from different angles"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Content generation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Parallel script writing, outlining, coding"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Log analysis"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Multiple agents analyze different log categories"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Model ensembling"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Multiple models produce outputs, aggregate votes"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Parallel code reading"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Multiple agents read different code sections"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fan-Out vs Fan-Out-Fan-In"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fan-Out Only"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Event → Multiple agents (parallel) → Each completes independently"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fan-Out-Fan-In"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Agent 1 (upstream) → Output\n    ↓\nFan-out to Agents 2, 3, 4 (concurrent)\n    ↓\nFan-in to Agent 5 (synthesize)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key difference"},{"type":"text","text":": Previous execution model activated one agent at a time; fan-out-fan-in treats agents as concurrent participants for that step, running them parallel before converging results downstream."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental Model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of event fan-out like "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"a restaurant kitchen receiving a large order"},{"type":"text","text":": instead of one chef cooking everything sequentially (slow), the order (event) is distributed to 5 chefs simultaneously (fan-out), each chef works on their dish independently (parallel processing), and then the dishes are plated together by the expeditor (fan-in/gather). If one chef is slow or has an issue, the other dishes still get ready."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fan-out = single event triggers multiple agents to execute concurrently in parallel"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"One input generates multiple outputs concurrently"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pattern: Fan-out (split task) → Execute (parallel) → Fan-in (gather + synthesize)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use when: strongly parallelizable tasks, multi-perspective exploration, high throughput, reduce latency"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Don't use when: strongly order-dependent, shared mutable state needed, tight budget"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implement via: AWS Step Functions (map state), Lambda concurrency, EventBridge, custom controller"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Before fanning out: give each branch distinct goal to avoid duplicated work"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Branches share read-only context by default, never workspace"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Gather does: deduplication, conflict detection, evidence merging — NOT naive concatenation"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Benefits: efficiency (parallel), scalability (independent), resilience (distributed), adaptability (real-time)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fan-out-on-write (push): immediate delivery to all targets; Fan-out-on-read (pull): on-demand fetching"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Track with events: fanout.started, branch.started/completed/timeout, gather.started/completed"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Configuration: concurrency, timeouts, cancellation, budget caps"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Agents scale the same way Lambda always has — if 500 research requests come in at once, you get 500 research agent functions running in parallel, and the outline agents don't even notice because they're completely independent."}]}]}}
